genresAdvancedInfo.name: karneval
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Karneval, also known as Carnival music, is a genre of music that originated in the Caribbean and is heavily influenced by African rhythms and European melodies. It is characterized by its use of percussion instruments such as steel drums, congas, and bongos, and features upbeat, energetic rhythms that are perfect for dancing. The lyrics often focus on celebration, love, and the joy of life.
